                            <comment id="12633962" author="bryanduxbury" created="Tue, 23 Sep 2008 23:08:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not positive (because I don&apos;t know how to repro the problem) but I think this should resolve the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12636069" author="bryanduxbury" created="Wed, 1 Oct 2008 15:42:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a slightly better version of a fix. It seems to get rid of the error in my testing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can someone please review and commit if it looks alright?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12636109" author="dreiss" created="Wed, 1 Oct 2008 18:06:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t really object to pulling the declaration of frameBuffer out of the try, but I don&apos;t see the point of it either.  I wonder if it would also be good to move the exception reporting above the close so that it happens even if there is some other sort of exception in the closing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12636452" author="bryanduxbury" created="Thu, 2 Oct 2008 20:23:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Good call. I changed the FrameBuffer declaration and printed the exception above the exception cleanup.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
